import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['lon'], data['lat'], c=data.index, cmap='viridis', label=data['state'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Longitude')
    ax.set_ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude across the US state capitals?', wrap=True)
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="States", loc="upper left", bbox_to_anchor=(1, 1))
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    min_lat_state = data.loc[data['lat'].idxmin()]['state']
    max_lat_state = data.loc[data['lat'].idxmax()]['state']
    min_lon_state = data.loc[data['lon'].idxmin()]['state']
    max_lon_state = data.loc[data['lon'].idxmax()]['state']

    min_lat = data['lat'].min()
    max_lat = data['lat'].max()
    min_lon = data['lon'].min()
    max_lon = data['lon'].max()

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(10, 6))

    ax[0].bar(['Min Latitude', 'Max Latitude'], [min_lat, max_lat], color=['blue', 'orange'])
    ax[0].set_ylabel('Latitude')
    ax[0].legend([f'Min: {min_lat:.2f} ({min_lat_state})', f'Max: {max_lat:.2f} ({max_lat_state})'])

    ax[1].bar(['Min Longitude', 'Max Longitude'], [min_lon, max_lon], color=['blue', 'orange'])
    ax[1].set_ylabel('Longitude')
    ax[1].legend([f'Min: {min_lon:.2f} ({min_lon_state})', f'Max: {max_lon:.2f} ({max_lon_state})'])

    plt.suptitle('Which state has the highest and lowest latitude and longitude values?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['first_letter'] = data['city'].apply(lambda x: x[0].upper())
    letter_counts = data['first_letter'].value_counts().sort_index()
    
    ax = letter_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='c', edgecolor='k')
    plt.title('What is the most common first letter of state capital city names?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('First Letter')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    max_count = letter_counts.max()
    max_letter = letter_counts.idxmax()
    plt.axhline(max_count, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Max: {max_letter} ({max_count:.2f})')
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import geopy.distance

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['lon'], data['lat'], c='blue', label='State Capitals')
    
    distances = []
    for i in range(len(data)):
        for j in range(i+1, len(data)):
            coord1 = (data.iloc[i]['lat'], data.iloc[i]['lon'])
            coord2 = (data.iloc[j]['lat'], data.iloc[j]['lon'])
            distance = geopy.distance.distance(coord1, coord2).km
            distances.append(distance)
            ax.plot([data.iloc[i]['lon'], data.iloc[j]['lon']], [data.iloc[i]['lat'], data.iloc[j]['lat']], c='gray', alpha=0.3)
            ax.text((data.iloc[i]['lon'] + data.iloc[j]['lon']) / 2, (data.iloc[i]['lat'] + data.iloc[j]['lat']) / 2, f"{distance:.2f} km", fontsize=8, alpha=0.5)
    
    avg_distance = sum(distances) / len(distances)
    ax.axhline(avg_distance, c='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Distance: {avg_distance:.2f} km')
    
    plt.title("What is the average distance between state capital cities?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def count_vowels(s):
    return sum(s.lower().count(v) for v in 'aeiou')

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['vowel_count'] = data['city'].apply(count_vowels)
    data = data.sort_values('vowel_count', ascending=False)
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(data['state'], data['vowel_count'], color='c')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Vowel Count')
    plt.title('Which state has the most and least number of vowels in its capital city name?', wrap=True)
    
    max_vowel_state = data.iloc[0]['state']
    min_vowel_state = data.iloc[-1]['state']
    max_vowel_count = data.iloc[0]['vowel_count']
    min_vowel_count = data.iloc[-1]['vowel_count']
    
    ax.axhline(max_vowel_count, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Max: {max_vowel_state} ({max_vowel_count})')
    ax.axhline(min_vowel_count, color='b', linestyle='--', label=f'Min: {min_vowel_state} ({min_vowel_count})')
    ax.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
